Constables Mmereki Mathekga and Thulani Mngomezulu were convicted last August after they attempted to conceal their involvement. JOHANNESBURG - Two Johannesburg police officers have been sentenced to 15 years in prison for the murder of a fellow officer three years ago.Constables Mmereki Mathekga and Thulani Mngomezulu were convicted last August after they attempted to conceal their involvement in the officer s murder and the attempted killing of another SAPS member.The Independent Police Investigative Directorate s Moses Dlamini said, Their version was that they were pursuing suspects who had shot at them and that the policeman shot by them whereas they were not even armed. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)